    "problemStatement": "Consider an array BBB of length MMM.\n\nWe define the prefix maximum array of array BBB, F(B)F(B)F(B), as an array CCC of length MMM such that Ci=max\u2061(B1,B2,\u2026Bi)C_i=\\max(B_1, B_2, \\ldots B_i)Ci\u200b=max(B1\u200b,B2\u200b,\u2026Bi\u200b).\n\nStack had a permutation PPP of length 2\u22c5N2 \\cdot N2\u22c5N. He deleted the last NNN elements from PPP to obtain an array PPP of size NNN.\n\nStack performs the following step for **all** permutations QQQ of length 2\u22c5N2 \\cdot N2\u22c5N :\n\n\nCheck whether Qi=PiQ_i = P_iQi\u200b=Pi\u200b for all 1\u2264i\u2264N1 \\leq i \\leq N1\u2264i\u2264N;\nIf the above condition is true, insert F(Q)F(Q)F(Q) in set ZZZ.\nFind the resultant size of set ZZZ.\n\nSince the value might be large, please print it modulo 998244353998244353998244353.\n\nNote that a permutation of length 2\u22c5N2\\cdot N2\u22c5N contains all integers from 111 to 2\u22c5N2\\cdot N2\u22c5N exactly once.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line of input will contain a single integer TTT, denoting the number of test cases.\nEach test case consists of multiple lines of input.\n\nThe first line of each test case contains an integer NNN \u2014 the current length of permutation PPP.\nThe next line contains NNN space-separated integers P1,P2,\u2026PNP_1, P_2, \\ldots P_NP1\u200b,P2\u200b,\u2026PN\u200b representing the first NNN elements of PPP.\n\n\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output on a new line the size of set ZZZ modulo 998244353998244353998244353.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u22641051 \\leq T \\leq 10^51\u2264T\u2264105",
